Political Capital: Hungarian Guard Increases State Risk
According to Political Capital’s Risk Analysis Division, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, founded this August with the support of the “Movement for a Better Hungary”, have raised the risk of Hungary and the region in several respects.
In connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk is the "enhancing of the already existing ethnic tensions between the Gypsies and non-gypsies in Hungary, which could even lead to violent ethnic conflicts in the short term".
The main reason for this is the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is probably aimed at the provocation of such a dispute, according to the research institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure on the part of the political leaders: "Persons of public life have left the discussion of the Roma question to representatives of radical political groups who have now built their political strategy on the Roma-Hungary set-up."
It is believed that this would exacerbate the problem, make reasonable dialogue impossible, favour extremities, and increase the likelihood of violent confrontations.
The research institute also believes that the activities of the Hungarian Guard had, not least thanks to the enormous attention of the domestic and foreign media, "the image of Hungary abroad seriously damaged, especially in terms of confidence in stability and democratic maturity".
We remember that since the fall of 2006, the reorganization of radical and extremely right-wing groups in Hungary has been constantly in the process of resurgence, so that since the summer of 2007, several organizations called the "National Self-Defense Association" have been founded.
"These groupings are common that they each define themselves as a civilian organization, while openly bragging about preparing their members for — sometimes armed — defense tasks (catastrophe protection, state defense, order protection), citing the inadequacy of the police, the army, or the state itself," it said.
And further: all this is done according to the method that tries to disguise various political aspirations as a bourgeois initiative based on the political and party-distortedness of the population.
