The integration of Slovak students in British schools is not possible.
In British schools, the number of children from countries in Eastern Europe is increasing, which causes local fears about the further development of the local school system.
The integration of Eastern Europeans has so far encountered a number of obstacles.
British schools even note cases where disputes between immigrants and the children of the original inhabitants increase in violence.
