Congress agrees to the MIFID directive, which came into force on November 1.
In parallel with the parliamentary drafting, which ended its session today with the Congressional resolution in the Senate on the supplementary/amendment proposals related to the project, the government published the provisions that emerge from the new law, with the intention of allowing the entry into force of both regulations until the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of Congress and Senate members who, in their negotiations and votes, had pursued the goal of establishing the best possible regulation, ensuring the safety of investors and regulating the individual entrepreneurial activities in order to guarantee a generally efficient market situation.
In addition to modernising the financial markets, MIFID, which redefines the Securities Services Regulation, is pursuing an improvement in investor protection, an increase in the control entitlement of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and the promotion of cooperation between the various control authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive enables both specialised companies and natural or legal persons to offer financial advice and also contributes to the creation of new financial services companies (ESIS), the advisory firms that join the investment and brokerage firms of securities.
In addition, it extends the number of financial transaction execution systems, adding to regulated circulation markets the multilateral securities trading systems and the internationalisation systems of trading orders, which would eventually enter into competition with the current economic operators.
The law obliges investment firms to inform the focus of their company profile, the confrontation and the forms of dealing with risks on the market and to register all projects carried out in order to facilitate the CNMV’s control task.
The Economic Commission of Congress subsequently proposed further changes, with the decision that the debt securities issued with titles must now be considered as complex financial resources for the investor due to their high level of risk, has been confirmed by the US mortgage and banking crisis.
In addition, the directive on the legal limitation of the working areas of qualified economists was adopted; 30 years after 1977, the regulation restricting the working areas reserved for economists was adopted.
The Senate, for its part, defined new positions in the financial sector, such as that of the economic mediator who works on foreign accounts, does not need authorization from the CNMV and can offer its services for the commercialization of products and for the acquisition of customers at the same time to several investment companies.
