Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which again depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driver's license, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
It is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you need to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to submit the corresponding compensation amount in case of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance that is composed of several factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to statistics, so that higher contribution payments are due in the event of a higher risk of accidents.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women need to make less contribution payments, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since, according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies, these tend to be fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefits that are attributed to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and therefore also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a whole range of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
At this point, we now list the most important points to consider when choosing an insurance policy in order to be able to make not only a performance, but also a price-oriented choice.
The under 25-year-olds encounter numerous obstacles when choosing cheap insurance, such as low driving practices and young driving licenses.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out full-cost insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full-cost with self-participation, so that while the benefits of a full-cost insurance are covered, they are offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer has to pay part of the amount caused by the damage himself.
The amount is set before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s principal representative at First Europe, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused on their own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is up to you to reduce insurance costs; this is how your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate at the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase in said tariffs.
The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it may allow itself to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to sign a contract, which is because with increasing driving practice, the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it is best to opt for a full-cost insurance with self-participation.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of the accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner is dropped.
Nevertheless, in the case of a married customer who does not have children, it is more advisable to take out full-time insurance; of course, only if it also allows the financial situation of the person concerned.
Insurers consider married couples with children to be customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly, their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, full insurance with self-involvement (with an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the event that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy is recommended, which only starts in the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to set up a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera states.
For pensioners, it is a good idea to take out a full-cost insurance with self-participation (with an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
In the end, you have to keep in mind that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs that require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
